oh yeah, there was that announcement a while ago
like, rules adivors or something?

Biggest thing I've noticed so far is how Jimmy makes JLK being on the CAG an advertising opportunity for them
Of course
BUT HE REDEEEMS HIMSELF WITH ABOUT PLANESWALKERS AS COMMANDERS
Does he though?
He argues for it, so yes
Does he?
Yup, I don't care if other people are against it :stuck_out_tongue: I want it
Do you though?
I'm blocking you
Are you though?
Wow, JLK just said we don't know what we really want
Well, let me rephrase that, he says we don't know what would happen if we get what we say we want
He's right
Except people house rule it now, so that's not 100% true
Blanket saying "You don't know how this thing will work out" is not right
But are they being degenerates about it like we know people would
I don't think we do
I mean, my group did it for 2 years and didn't care or notice much shift in power
Just imagine an entire room of Don's doing dirty shit with those walkers?
Because people don't share Don's playstyle now without planeswalkers?
If they do make the chang, I'm building Bant-iyo right away though
I'm saying that playstyle empowered to do planeswalkery stuff that much easier, with less hoops to jump through I think it gets out of hand that much easier
I don't because there's still the same kind of degenerate play styles without Planeswalkers as Commanders
I mean, we got to having cEDH with turn 2 win games without Planeswalkers. And that's not a knock at cEDH, it's just an observation of the difference without changing the rule
Everyone's argument is basically based on speculation and no one's willing to even try it temporarily because it's too hard to change and it's just a boring argument
I mean I agree with him on keeping off-color fetches. I don't even do it, but I don't see the problem with it. It's how the rules work and it isn't broken
Im going to but up jokulhaups for when the planeswalker argmageddon comes
Again, I'd be satisfied if they did the same thing they did with Unstable and made it legal for a month or whatever to see what happens
How many people actually got into it though knowing it wouldn’t last? I know a couple random at my old shop didn’t want to spend real money on something they could only do for a very short time
Same with planeswalkers. How many people would build a brand new deck only to not be able to play it in a month when CZ already did a ton of damage to what brawl could have been
Also, did they say “the last game night?”
ewww for Planeswalkers as Commanders.
Fun in Brawl, but 10 extra life is a lot when you have a lifegain spell in the command zone that also has an addendum on it that says "oh yeah, you win the game"

That argument doesn't translate to this topic Matt. Not buying unstable and not building new decks aren't the same. How many people have Planeswalkers in their collection? It costs nothing (but maybe time) to test it
I'm actually for the Unstable Commanders, too. And I was venomously against the temporary thing at first
WOW
Unstable had NINE legendary creatures
